  "local_port": 58374,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I know if someone blocks me on Facebook messenger?",
  "response": "If someone has blocked you on Facebook Messenger, it can be difficult to confirm directly, as Facebook does not explicitly notify you when someone blocks you. However, there are several signs and behaviors that can hint that you may have been blocked. Here\u2019s how to check:\n\n---\n\n### **Signs You Might Be Blocked on Facebook Messenger**\n1. **Unable to Find Their Profile in Messenger**:\n   - Search for their name in the Messenger app. If their profile doesn\u2019t appear, they may have blocked you or deactivated their account.\n\n2. **Messages Not Delivered**:\n   - Messages you send to the person will not be delivered (you\u2019ll see a single gray checkmark instead of a double blue checkmark).\n   - If you were previously able to send messages and now see a \"This person isn\u2019t available right now\" message, it could indicate a block.\n\n3. **Unable to Call or Video Chat**:\n   - If you try to call or video chat with them, the call will not go through, and you may see an error message.\n\n4. **Profile Picture and Status Updates Disappear**:\n   - If you can no longer see their profile picture, last active status, or any status updates, they may have blocked you.\n\n5. **Search for Their Facebook Profile**:\n   - Try searching for their profile on Facebook (not Messenger). If you can\u2019t find their profile, they may have blocked you. However, they could also have deactivated their account or changed privacy settings.\n\n6. **Mutual Friends\u2019 List**:\n   - Check mutual friends\u2019 lists to see if their profile appears there. If it doesn\u2019t, they may have blocked you.\n\n---\n\n### **Important Notes**\n- **Deactivated vs. Blocked**: If someone has deactivated their Facebook account, their profile and messages will disappear temporarily, but this doesn\u2019t mean they\u2019ve blocked you.\n- **Privacy Settings**: Some users restrict their profiles or messages to friends only, which may prevent you from seeing their profile or sending messages.\n- **No Official Confirmation**: Facebook does not provide a direct way to confirm if someone has blocked you, so these methods are based on indirect clues.\n\nIf you suspect you\u2019ve been blocked, it\u2019s best to respect the other person\u2019s boundaries and avoid trying to contact them through other means.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
